content:
This module provides functions for managing user billing subscriptions and usage within the DocMed application.

## Key Exports

*   **`SubscriptionStatus`**: A type alias representing the possible statuses of a subscription.
*   **`SubscriptionDoc`**: An interface defining the structure of a subscription document in Firestore.
*   **`UsageDoc`**: An interface defining the structure of a usage document in Firestore.
*   **`getSubscription(userId: string)`**: Retrieves the subscription document for a given user.
*   **`upsertSubscription(userId: string, data: Partial<Omit<SubscriptionDoc, "updatedAt">>)`**: Creates or updates a user's subscription document.
*   **`getUsage(userId: string)`**: Retrieves the usage document for a given user.
*   **`resetUsageIfNeeded(userId: string, periodEnd: number | null)`**: Resets monthly usage if the current billing cycle has ended.
*   **`incrementMonthlyInits(userId: string, limit: number)`**: Increments the monthly init count for a user and throws an error if the limit is reached.
*   **`ensureTrialSubscription(userId: string)`**: Ensures that a user has a trial subscription if one doesn't already exist.
*   **`hasProcessedStripeEvent(userId: string, eventId: string)`**: Checks if a Stripe event has already been processed for a user.
*   **`markStripeEventProcessed(userId: string, eventId: string)`**: Marks a Stripe event as processed for a user.

## Usage Example

```typescript
import { getSubscription, upsertSubscription, getUsage, incrementMonthlyInits } from './subscription';

async function manageUserSubscription(userId: string) {
  // Get current subscription
  const subscription = await getSubscription(userId);
  console.log('Current subscription:', subscription);

  // Example of updating a subscription (e.g., after a Stripe webhook event)
  // await upsertSubscription(userId, { status: 'active', tier: 'pro' });

  // Get usage data
  const usage = await getUsage(userId);
  console.log('Current usage:', usage);

  // Increment monthly inits, assuming a limit of 100
  try {
    await incrementMonthlyInits(userId, 100);
    console.log('Monthly inits incremented.');
  } catch (error: any) {
    if (error.code === 'init_limit') {
      console.error('User has reached their monthly init limit.');
    } else {
      throw error;
    }
  }
}
```
